cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.AR 

The paper discusses a new type confusion and memory error sanitizer for C/C++ programs, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The focus on detecting memory errors and exploits suggests a potential fit for the categories of security and cryptography (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of low-fat pointers and type meta data may also align with the category of architecture (cs.AR).
